The backyard needed cleaning. I stood on the deck, rearranging flowers and pots, when I noticed balls rolling across the grass around me. “What the hell is wrong with the earth?” I thought. The ground beneath me swayed back and forth, as if we were on a boat. I tried to get a better look at my neighbour’s garden, leaning against a glass door that had suddenly appeared. But before I knew it, I fell right through and landed over their fence. I climbed back to my backyard using vines—only to do it again. And once again, I tumbled into my neighbor’s yard. A lady stepped outside and asked, “Are you okay? Want to see my pets?” She led me to a collection of stacked tanks, each filled with an assortment of creatures—fish, birds, reptiles, even bunnies. i said wow staring in amazement.

We passed by many lakes and mountains, and next to them stood a huge church. We secretly climbed up a small path and made our way to the top of the church. We walked along the edge of the church roof, seemingly without any fear of falling.

I dreamed that my parents got divorced, and we didn’t split any property. My mom remarried someone else, but I really disliked that person. I didn’t know him before, but I just felt very uncomfortable and unhappy about it.
I dreamed last night that my friend and I were working in a factory. I also dreamed that there seemed to be an archaeological site in the factory. I can’t quite remember what exactly happened
I dreamed that my boyfriend and I went to a park, where we were learning how to skateboard. It was a very normal and short dream.

dreamed that my friend and I went to the hospital because he had an allergic reaction to something, but we didn’t know what it was. We waited in line for a long time before seeing the doctor, and it turned out to be nothing serious. However, suddenly, I broke out in a rash that looked like sharp spikes.

I dreamed that my mom was taking drugs, and later, for some reason, I fell into the water. I couldn’t swim, and there were many police officers chasing me. In the end, I was arrested because my mom reported me. I had no choice but to give up my studies.

I dreamed that my friend Zach was crying and telling me how much he missed me, saying he wanted to be friends again. I realized that I was dreaming within a dream, but when I woke up from that dream, I found that he had actually said those words to me. In reality, he still ran away.

I dreamed of a missing girl case. While searching in an abandoned building, I found a moving, faceless mannequin that resembled the girl. At its feet were two boxes with the skeletons of a boy and a girl. Our parents were shocked, but the remains weren’t hers.I overheard the mother threatening the father for money or she’d kill the girl. When we tried to stop them, we were thrown back in time to a past murder. Later, a flood hit, and we struggled to survive.In the end, the parents ate the two children, and the girl also died. They weren’t human. The mother hunted us during the day, forcing us to hide in darkness, while the father hunted at night, making us stay in the light. We tried to escape by boat, but some people helped them capture others. I don’t remember what happened next
I dreamed that my friend gave me flowers, which he had never done before. He held them in his arms the whole way, and by the time he gave them to me, they had already wilted.

In my dream, I was playing the game Werewolf with my friends, and I was assigned the role of the villain. I’m really bad at lying, so I felt super guilty throughout the game. I kept trying to dodge their questions as they tried to test whether I was the killer. But in the end, I realized I just couldn’t keep up the act anymore, so I had to admit I was the killer. Except… it wasn’t actually a game. It turned out to be a real confrontation between a detective and a murderer—because in the dream, I had actually killed someone.

I dreamt I was performing on a huge outdoor ice rink, with a crowd of faceless people watching. I knew I wasn’t ready, but the music had already started. I was wearing the wrong skates, and the ice beneath me felt too slick, starting to crack. Every step felt like I might fall. Everyone was staring, and I completely blanked on my routine—just frozen there, heart pounding like I couldn’t breathe.

I’m standing by an old, broken ship. Wind howling. The deck creaks. No one around. Just objects—frozen in time. I step inside. Rooms, dusty, untouched. A mirror. I look in—It’s not me.The water rises. Cold, up to my knees.I run.No doors. Only silence.And the sound of something breathing behind me.

I think I was near the ocean… sitting on a rock? Or holding one.The wind was loud. I remember that.I was talking—maybe to the rock?No one else was there.At some point there were words… carved on it? Or floating?I don’t know what they said. But it felt important.Then I think I dropped it.Or maybe I just woke up.
We were on a train. I think it was going to Montreal.Or nowhere.My boyfriend was sitting next to me, but his face kept changing—familiar, then not.He gave me something, a box maybe.I didn’t open it.
We brought the cat to the park. She was playing in the grass.Then she disappeared.We searched everywhere—under benches, behind trees.The park felt bigger than before.

I was in a regular store—maybe a bookstore or a 7-Eleven.But in the corner, there was an Aikatsu! machine.I swiped my student card, and somehow it worked.The first card that came out glowed gold—it was a super rare outfit card, purple and sparkling. Limited edition, I think.I shouted, “I got it!” but no one reacted.Next thing I knew, I was on stage, wearing the outfit.Lights everywhere. It looked like a new version of the Starlight Academy stage.

I was in Milan, at the Winter Olympics.Front row at the figure skating event.The ice was glowing. Someone jumped—everyone cheered.I looked down—I was wearing skates.Then I heard my name over the speakers.I wasn’t watching anymore.I was next.

I was back in high school. Everything looked smaller.I remember feeling heavy, like I couldn’t breathe right.My mom was there, saying, “You need to focus. No distractions.”I turned to look for my best friend, but she was already walking away.I tried to follow, but something was pulling me back—maybe her hand, maybe just fear.The hallway kept stretching.I called out her name, but no sound came out.Then I was alone.And I think I started crying, but only on the inside.

I was with him again—my older friend.It felt like before, when things were simple.We were walking through some kind of shopping street. The sun was low, soft.He bought me ice cream—my favorite flavor, I think.I laughed about something, maybe nothing.Then I saw it—a poster of my favorite idol, tucked behind some magazines.He got it for me without asking.

I had the suit, the gloves, the big mesh hood—like the kind beekeepers wear.I was out in the field, surrounded by tall grass and buzzing.So many bugs. Crawling, flying, landing on my notes.I kept telling myself, “It’s okay. This is my job.”But I was terrified.One of them looked me in the eyes. I swear it did.I wanted to dig in the ground for pottery, not… follow beetles.But everyone in the dream seemed to think I was good at this.So I kept going.

I found my old teddy bear—the one I broke as a kid.It was lying under a bed, stitched clumsily, one eye missing.I picked it up, and for a second, it felt like it blinked.I don’t remember how it got there.But it still smelled like home.

In the dream, my parents weren’t divorced yet—but it felt close.The house was quiet, like something already ended.My brother and I just sat there, not saying much.We acted like we didn’t care.But I think we just didn’t know what to do.

I really love The Little Prince—it’s also the theme of my figure skating program.I dreamt I had crossed into the world of the Little Prince.I asked the pilot,“Has the Little Prince really left his planet?Has he left his own heart, too?”

dreamt I was sick and couldn’t go to school.But it was a really busy week—my presentation, group project, a paper to write.I kept checking the deadlines, feeling overwhelmed.Then my professor told me I was lying.That I wasn’t really sick.He said I’d get a zero for everything.I tried to explain, but my voice wouldn’t come out.No one believed me.

I dreamt I met Yuzuru Hanyu—the skater who first inspired me.He was standing right in front of me, looking almost the same, but not quite.I wanted to say something, anything.But I didn’t know what.Since his retirement, he’s changed.I guess I was disappointed.But I couldn’t tell him that.So I just walked away—quickly, pretending I didn’t see him.

It was late, and we went to the convenience store together.The streets were empty and quiet.I picked out snacks, he paid.We sat on a bench outside, sharing a can of something fizzy.I said, “I should be writing.”He said, “You can write tomorrow.”

We were lying on the school field, just the two of us.The grass was cool, and the sky was full of stars—too many to count.My best friend pointed out constellations, even if they weren’t real.We talked about nothing and everything.I didn’t check the time.I just hoped the night wouldn’t end.

My phone was broken. The screen kept flickering.I tried calling my boyfriend, my friend, my brother.No one picked up.Messages unsent. Notifications blank.I wasn’t sure if I still existed.Everything was silent, except the ticking of a clock I couldn’t find.

When I looked into a store window, my reflection was missing. A child that looked like me tugged at my sleeve and whispered, "You're not supposed to be here." Then, I woke up

I was on a spaceship drifting through the galaxy. Stars whizzed past the windows, and outside, planets glowed in unfamiliar colors. A voice crackled over the intercom, saying, "We have arrived." But when I looked out again, Earth was gone. The controls wouldn’t work, and my weight started disappearing. As I floated upward, I woke up.

I was running through an endless hallway lined with doors, but none of them would open. Behind me, footsteps echoed, getting closer. I didn’t dare look back. The hallway suddenly turned into an open field, but the footsteps continued. I braced myself for something to grab me, but just before it did, I woke up.

I was sitting in my grandmother’s kitchen, the smell of freshly baked bread filling the air. She was humming an old tune, her hands busy kneading dough. When she looked up at me, she smiled but didn’t say a word. I wanted to ask her something, but the words wouldn’t come out. Then, the kitchen faded, and I woke up.

dreams.summary: I was inside a massive library with books stacked to the ceiling. No matter which way I turned, the shelves rearranged themselves, blocking the exit. The more I searched, the more lost I became. Finally, I pulled a book from the shelf, and inside was a map with an ‘X’ marked on it. I followed it, but before I reached my destination, I woke up.

I was in a candy land where the rivers flowed with chocolate, and the trees sprouted cotton candy. Every step I took left footprints made of sprinkles. A talking marshmallow guided me to a castle made of gingerbread, but just as I was about to enter, the world started melting, and I woke up.

I was in my bedroom, but something felt off. The shadows moved on their own, stretching unnaturally along the walls. When I tried to turn on the light, it flickered but didn’t stay on. A whisper echoed from the darkest corner, saying my name. I reached for my phone, but my hands passed through it. Then, I woke up.

I was in a futuristic city where every building was made of mirrors. People walked past, but their reflections didn’t match their movements. A giant screen in the sky displayed my face, and a robotic voice announced, "Welcome home." But I didn’t recognize the place. When I tried to ask someone where I was, they all pointed at the screen. Then, I woke up.

I walked through a door and found myself in a room filled with different versions of me. Some were older, some younger. One had bright blue hair, another wore glasses. They all turned to look at me and said in unison, "Which path do you choose?" Before I could answer, I woke up.

dreams.summary: I was walking on clouds, each step soft like a cushion. Birds with golden feathers flew past, singing in a language I almost understood. dreams.summary: I met someone I hadn’t seen in years. We talked, laughed, and walked through an empty city together. I knew it wasn’t real, but I didn’t want to leave. When I turned away for a second and looked back, they were gone. A note was left behind: "See you in another dream." Then, I woke up.

I found a small door at the back of my closet. When I opened it, it led to a staircase spiraling downward. I kept descending, passing doors labeled with years from the past and future. I hesitated at one marked with my birth year but decided against opening it. When I reached the bottom, I woke up.

I was in a city being swallowed by rising water. People scrambled to rooftops, but I had a map with an escape route. I followed it to a bridge that led to a dry land, but as I crossed, the bridge started to crumble. I jumped—and woke up mid-air.

I found a hidden garden inside a cave, glowing with bioluminescent plants. A small creature with silver eyes gestured for me to follow it. It led me to a fountain where the water reflected a different world. I reached out, but before I could touch it, I woke up.

I was trying to speak, but every word came out as gibberish. No one could understand me. I wrote on a piece of paper, but the letters rearranged themselves. Just as I started panicking, someone whispered in my ear, "You know the language; you just forgot it." Then, I woke up.

I was being chased by someone I trusted. No matter how fast I ran, they were always right behind me. I ducked into a hidden alley, but they were already there, smiling. "Why are you running?" they asked. Before I could answer, I woke up.

I was given a chance to relive a moment I regretted. This time, I said everything I had wanted to say. As I spoke, I felt lighter, as if a weight was being lifted. The person smiled, and I woke up with tears in my eyes.

I stood at the edge of the universe, staring into an endless expanse of stars. A voice behind me whispered, "Do you want to see more?" I nodded, and galaxies unfolded before me. Just as I stepped forward, I woke up.
I was a talking cat leading a parade of dancing penguins through a city made of cheese. That’s it. That’s the dream. Then, I woke up.
I was walking with a random girl I knew briefly in highschool through what seemed to be a park we had some kind of discussion (then I began to wake up)

I was on some type of island with my best friend and my boyfriend. There were fire pits and tiki torches. There was also a pool that we were all swimming in. I was in a in an airplane with my boyfriend. We travelled somewhere tropical but I can’t remember exactly where it was. We drank drinks out of coconuts of the beach - and swam

I was on my way to class but for some reason I couldn’t get there in time (it was as if my movement were standing still but time kept moving) so I was really late and was really stressed about it. I missed something important and got into trouble with my professor

That I was working as a therapist and was meeting with a client who was really upset. I know I was able to help them and they left the session In a better place than they arrived. I cannot recall exactly what we “talked about”.

I was once again late to an important meeting with a professor/advisor (I couldn’t tell who exactly the authority figure was). Even though the person wasn’t upset I was, and I woke up very anxious and stressed
I had a dream that I had a family and kids, and was currently pregnant, I was a stay at home mom and I had partner that got home from work. I remember feeling fulfilled

I had a dream that I found a stuffed animal from where I was a child in an attic - I was emotional in the dream but I never had a very sentimental toy from when I was a child so it was a strange feeling.
I had a dream that I was “grown up” living in a big white house with a pool. I was married to my current partner. We both were professionals and had a good relationship and home
I had a dream that I was famous to some extent. I had a lot of followers on social media and was recognized when I walked out in public

I had a dream about an assignment (essay) that I was working on for a class. In my dream I was able to get through the paper really quickly (sadly this wasn’t the case in real life). I was sitting on my couch with my boyfriend while working on the paper.

I was out for st Patrick’s day with my friends walking downtown. We were all really drunk but having a good time. I don’t remember specially what bars we went to but I know we were taking shots with other groups that were out to celebrate the holiday.
I was having an intimate encounter with my boyfriend that went on for what felt like hours. We were both enjoying ourselves and it was taking place in my house in my bedroom

My best friend came to visit me in Toronto and we went out clubbing. We had a really amazing time and drank a lot
That I fell off a really high ledge. The dream woke me up and I had a pit in my stomach. I don’t remember anything before seeing the edge of the ledge and then falling

dreams.summary: I am sitting in my 7th grade class alone at lunch. I felt buzzing in the background so I turned around and saw my friends laughing together. They were whispering and I heard my name being said. I felt my heart drop, I felt like I shouldn’t have heard that because it hurt my feelings, but I thought they were my friends. I tried to ignore it but I heard my name again, “Why did Mckayla turn around? I’m really not trying to look at her face right now”. They continued to speak about me and keep saying my name as if it was impossible for me to hear what they were saying even though I was sat at the row of desks in front of them. I wanted to stand up for myself and confront them but I forgot how to speak. I turn to the person next to me, and it’s my teacher sending me to the principals office.

I am walking home from the gym late at night and it is really hot outside. It was really quiet but I could hear the animals around me, the raccoons and skunks, and a squirrel ran past me. Then I heard footsteps behind me, I turn around and I don’t see anyone. I keep walking but the footsteps sound like they’re getting closer. I start to run and I’m too scared to look back. I kept trying to run and turn at random corners but they kept close, and I was starting to get tired. A hand grabs my wrist, and it’s a man in a hood but I can’t see his face. I try to slip out of his grip and I took up again and it’s my cat’s vet telling me I have to pay another $1000 for surgical complications for a surgery she had last year.

I had an older sister, which felt odd because in reality I am the oldest daughter. She was a teenager and I was much younger, around 10 years old. My parents were going away for the weekend and left me with my older sister. She was suddenly being really mean to me and told me to go to the basement to get her a drink from the cooler. I tried to come upstairs but the door was locked. I could hear a party happening upstairs with scary music. Someone opens the door for me and I see a bunch of teenagers in costumes for halloween, having a party and drinking. My sister sees me and yells at me in front of everyone, then makes me sit in the corner in the backyard. I sat there and cried for the rest of the night.

I am on a cruise vacation with my family and 2 friends. We were at dinner one day and I decided to step out to look at the view. Suddenly, the weather got bad. It started to rain and the tides were getting higher and higher. I felt it touch my feet and I was holding onto the railing for dear life. The door closed behind me so I ran to another part of the deck floor to take cover but I didn’t make it in time. I look at my feet and I see a jellyfish that had made it onto the ship. I try to run back inside again but I was too late and got dragged into the ocean. I look at the glass and see my mom at the window screaming for me as I fall backward into the cold water. Everything goes black, and then I woke up.

I felt an enormous amount of guilt but I didn’t know what to say, or if i should say anything at all.

I woke up suddenly, in a rush to get to school because for some strangle reason my alarm didn’t go off. I wore my school uniform and carpooled with my friend. Once I got there, everyone was wearing regular clothing and I was so embarrassed that I missed civvies day. I felt out of place all day.

dreams.summary: Took place in a school setting. School resembled my high school, but it was mostly unfamiliar. Was with a friend at a table (likely studying together). Tried to organize my school notes on my computer. Struggled to decide how to organize. Tried to remember how I did it before, but couldn’t get a clear plan. Someone came up to me and started to judge my note organization and the fact that I was organizing in the 1st place. Don’t remember exactly what was said, but it was something along the lines of “why are you doing that?” and “it’s a waste of time”. Tried to defend myself, but couldn’t find the words to do so. Stuff happened before and after this, but I don’t remember.

Was with someone random and tried to navigate a tight underground area. Reminds me of an old mineshaft in caves mixed with a basement cellar that became a maze. Many tunnels, nooks, dead-ends, etc. Incoherent pathways. Never walked the same path twice. Colourful monster made of clay chased us. Tried to escape. Monster kept switching between hostile and friendly. Friendly when we were far away from it, but hostile when close. Spent what felt like hours trying to navigate. Some areas were interesting. Stairs that didn’t lead anywhere. Large ravine with wooden beams bridges. Safe nooks that the monster couldn’t fit in or reach. Caverns with scattered plushies and toys. Encountered fairy-like creatures, but don’t remember the interaction. We never got caught, but we never really escaped.
